

  Solution

  1. HTMX Form Submission - The form now uses HTMX instead of traditional POST:
  **{
      "hx-post": "/askesis/submit-message",
      "hx-target": "#conversation-messages",
      "hx-swap": "beforeend",
      "hx-on::after-request": "document.getElementById('conversation-input').value = ''",
  }

  2. New UI Endpoint - Created /askesis/submit-message that:
    - Accepts form data (not JSON)
    - Returns HTML (not JSON)
    - Appends both user message and AI response to the conversation
    - Uses a mock response for now (ready to integrate with actual AI service)

  3. Conversation Container - Added id="conversation-messages" so HTMX knows where to append new messages

  How It Works Now

  When you click "Send Message":
  1. ✅ HTMX intercepts the form submission (no page redirect)
  2. ✅ POSTs to /askesis/submit-message
  3. ✅ Gets back HTML with your message + AI response
  4. ✅ Appends it to the conversation area
  5. ✅ Clears the input field
  6. ✅ Stays on the same page!

  This is exactly how Claude.ai works - messages appear in the conversation without page reloads.

  Test It

  Navigate to http://localhost:8000/askesis and try sending a message. You should see:
  - Your message appears in the conversation
  - AI responds immediately
  - Input field clears automatically
  - No page redirect!
